<L>__{exterior forest encampment night}
<A>__{a commotion; the nobles, their heads hooded, are led in on horseback by guerrillas from the village. the nobles stop, feel their hoods pulled off, and see wallace.}
<C>__{craig}
<D>__{sir william. we come to seek a meeting.}
<C>__{wallace}
<D>__{you've all sworn to longshanks.}
<C>__{craig}
<D>__{an oath to a liar is no oath at all. an oath to a patriot is a vow indeed. every man of us is ready to swear loyalty to you.}
<C>__{wallace}
<D>__{so let the council swear publicly.}
<C>__{craig}
<D>__{we cannot. some scarcely believe you are alive. other think you'll pay them mornay's wages. we bid you to edinburgh. meet us at the city gates, two days from now, at sunset. pledge us your pardon and we will unite behind you. scotland will be one.}
<A>__{wallace glances at hamish and stephen, who can barely hide their contempt. wallace looks at the nobles.}
<C>__{wallace}
<D>__{i will meet you, but only one way if robert the bruce is there, and puts his hand on my bible, and swears his loyalty to scotland.}
<C>__{craig}
<D>__{he has already agreed to come.}
